0I%20had%20already%20changed%20my%20name%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b9ce61c-55f0-4ebb-9266-9daf9ae42d3e%5C%22%3EIt%20wasn't%20my%20first%20last%20name%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20name%20when%20I%20met%20my%20husband%20wasn't%20the%20one%20I%20was%20born%20with.%20Ironically%2C%20in%20my%20late%20teens%2C%20I'd%20already%20gone%20through%20a%20name%20change%20after%20a%20short-lived%20first%20marriage.%20My%20maiden%20name%20had%20been%20a%20mouthful%20that%20people%20always%20messed%20up%2C%20so%20adopting%20a%20simpler%20one%20was%20a%20relief.%20Plus%2C%20no%20one%20in%20my%20immediate%20family%20shared%20my%20last%20name.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-maiden-name-middle-names-family-legacy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emom%20had%20given%20me%20her%20maiden%20name%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20she%20remarried%20and%20took%20my%20stepfather's%20last%20name%2C%20as%20did%20my%20half-brother%2C%20whom%20they%20had%20together.%20I%20was%20the%20only%20one%20left%20with%20a%20hard%20name%20no%20one%20else%20seemed%20to%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20I%20had%20changed%20my%20name%20before%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20reason%2C%20didn't%20sit%20well%20with%20my%20soon-to-be%20husband.%20If%20I%20had%20changed%20it%20before%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20why%20wouldn't%20I%20be%20willing%20to%20change%20it%20again%3F%20This%20time%2C%20for%20him.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20personal%20slight%2C%20which%20I%20understood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%2C%20my%20husband%20comes%20from%20a%20large%2C%20close-knit%20family%20who%20do%20all%20share%20the%20same%20last%20name.%20Every%20summer%2C%20they%20gather%20in%20the%20hundreds%20for%20a%20family%20reunion%20and%20have%20streets%20named%20after%20them%20in%20towns%20sprinkled%20across%20the%20Western%20Slope%20of%20Colorado.%20As%20an%20only%20child%2C%20he%20felt%20we%20needed%20to%20carry%20on%20the%20name%20for%20his%20family%20branch%20by%20having%20me