se%20name%20we%20should%20give%20them%20or%20if%20we%20should%20hyphenate.%20And%20I've%20realized%20that%20my%20last%20name%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20personality.%20If%20that%20means%20I%20have%20to%20spell%20it%20an%20extra%20time%20or%20two%2C%20the%20trade-off%20is%20now%20worth%20it%20in%20my%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223054d99a-ed1d-4de3-8a2a-847ca8535a1a%5C%22%3EThese%20days%2C%20however%2C%20my%20husband%20has%20had%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20about%20the%20situation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20my%20husband%20apologized%20to%20me%20for%20%26quot%3Bmaking%26quot%3B%20me%20change%20my%20name.%20He%20mentioned%20how%20silly%20he%20thought%20his%20reasonings%20were%20now%2C%20that%20he%20understood%20having%20the%20same%20last%20name%20is%20kind%20of%20arbitrary.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20affects%20literally%20no%20part%20of%20our%20lives%20together%20in%20a%20substantial%20way.%20My%20favorite%20realization%20that%20he%20mentioned%20was%20how%20our%20love%20is%20so%20much%20greater%20than%20a%20shared%20last%20name.%20Then%2C%20he%20asked%20if%20I'd%20like%20to%20change%20my%20name%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thought%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20ease%20of%20%26quot%3BChilds%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20last%20name%20has%20its%20appeal%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20help%20but%20laugh.%20I%20have%20zero%20desire%20to%20go%20through%20that%20paperwork%20again.%20Not%20unless%20he%20wants%20to%20revisit%20that%20original%20idea%20of%20picking%20a%20brand-new%20name%20together.%20And%20he's%20willing%20to%20file%20the%20forms%20himself%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-last-name-because-husband-asked-me-to-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751821082000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682f7fb8ca50259add4cd531%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.