with%20an%20average%20total%20cholesterol%20around%20200%20mg%2FdL)%20into%20a%20heart-healthy%20range%20(186%20mg%2FdL).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c6ce552-8e52-49b1-adb1-a45b99abe0a9%5C%22%3EChickpeas%20have%20cholesterol-lowering%20power%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22chickpeas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6866c2ff85e81483682d5c59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221180%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChickpeas%20are%20rich%20in%20phytosterols%2C%20a%20cholesterol-lowering%20plant%20compound.%3Cp%3Emargouillatphotos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20why%20different%20beans%20house%20different%20health%20benefits%20probably%20has%20to%20do%20with%20the%20chemicals%20that%20color%20them%20and%20make%20each%20bean%20unique.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20phytochemicals%20that%20make%20black%20beans%20black%20are%20known%20to%20have%20more%20anti-inflammatory%20properties%2C%20golden%20chickpeas%20have%20more%20of%20other%20plant%20chemicals%20called%20phytosterols%2C%20which%20are%20cholesterol-lowering%20compounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fdiet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enutrition%3C%2Fa%3E%20buffs%20often%20recommend%20eating%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20different%20colored%20plants%2C%20including%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20beans%20and%20whole%20grains.%20By%20eating%20a%20rich%20diversity%20of%20colorful%20whole%20foods%2C%20you'll%20enjoy%20the%20complex%20natural%20%26quot%3Bfood%20matrix%26quot%3B%20found%20inside%20each%20one%2C%20lead%20researcher%20Indika%20Edirisinghe%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20contains%20protein%2C%20it%20contains%20lipid%2C%20it%20contains%20fiber%2C%20vitamins%2C%20minerals%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20different%20combinations%20of%20each%20from%20bean%20to%20bean%2C%20he%20said.%20%26qu